feed.title: Lerderderg State Park - Moths
feed.subtitle: Parks Victoria describes this State Park as follows: Rising in the Great Dividing Range, the Lerderderg River has cut a 300 metre deep gorge through sandstone and slate, almost bisecting the park. The park has a wide variety of vegetation and wildlife and some interesting relics of goldmining. Moths are just part of the unique fauna

entry.title: Trachydora spp.
entry.content: The name cannot be found. It is similar to Trachydora centromela and there may be dimorphism. It is currently listed as Trachydora sp. (5) in the MoV data base.

entry.title: Zonopetala correcta
entry.content: Correct name is Zonopetala correcta Differs from Z. decisana by the yellowish tinge of the basal third of forewing and the size and shape of the large dark patch enclosed by an irregular white line on the outer quarter of the forewing.
